The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Two warehouses and a medicine store on Howrah Maidan were gutted in a fire on Monday, causing damage of over Rs 1.5 lakh. No one was injured.

 he cause of the fire has not been established. Six fire tenders took about five hours to douse the flames.

 n official of the Howrah Improvement Trust said the fire was caused by a CESC transformer blast.

 The Howrah Government Railway Police launched a taxi ?complaint card? at Howrah station on Monday. The cards will be distributed free from police booths at the station and can be used to lodge complaints against taxi drivers.

 About 30 contract teachers of government-run technology colleges, who had launched a hunger strike outside Bikash Bhavan demanding confirmation of their jobs, will be allowed to seek permanent employment in their respective institutions through the state public service commission.

 A Baranagar-based postal department staff was arrested on Sunday on the charge of murdering a housewife.

 Howrah police seized 7.5 kg of raw silver from two persons during a raid on a house on GR Road on Monday morning.

 Ranjit Ray, 35, was arrested in Barasat on Monday for furnishing false documents to enrol his name in the voters? list.

